org.tms.api.derivables

Interface Operator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Labeled
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    org.tms.teq.AbstractOp, AbstractOperator, AsynchronousOp, RestConsumerOp, StockTickerOp, SynchronousOp

    public interface Operator
extends Labeled
    A class implements the Operator interface to act as an operator in a calculation expression assigned to a Derivable object. Operators can act as functions that take zero or more arguments and return a value, or as a unary or binary operator that acts on one (unary) or two (binary) values and returns a value. Arguments and returned values can be any valid Java data type, including other objects of your own design.

    Operator precedence in the TMS system is expressed using a numeric integer priority. The values used are as follows:

    OperatorsPriorityExamples
    Parens10(, )
    Functions8built-in and user-defined functions
    Unary7!, %, -, neg
    Multiplicative6*, /
    Additive5+, -
    Relational4>, <, >=, <=
    Equality3=, ==, !=, <>
    Logical2&&, ||

    By default, user-defined operators are assigned a priority of 8. This can be overridden, as needed.
    Since:
    "1.0"
    Version:
    "1.3"
